Fields.Description:
This fields indicates if the record is currently restricted. It defaults to 0 (indicating that the record is unrestricted).


The value in this field is used to drive functionality that depends on whether the record is currently restricted (e.g., display of the ‘RESTRICTED RECORD’ banner).


The value is automatically updated by Pathways when a user with access completes any of the following actions:


  •  Restricts the record using the Restrict Access button – resulting in a status change to 1 (record restricted).
  •  Un-restricts the record using the Un-Restrict Access button – resulting in a status change to 0 (record un-restricted).
  •  Approves a request submitted via the Request Record Restriction button – resulting in a status change to 1.
  • Approves a request submitted via the Un-Request Record Restriction button – resulting in a status change to 0.
